  <!-- Glossary -->

  <div class="book-section">
    <div class="section-head"><span class="sec-roman">Glossary</span><h2>Glossary of Operators and Terms</h2></div>
    <p style="font-family:'IM Fell English',serif;font-style:italic;font-size:0.91rem;color:var(--ash);margin-bottom:22px;line-height:1.68;">Entries are listed in order of structural priority within the system, beginning with the primitive operators and proceeding to derived and applied terms.</p>
    <div class="gloss-list">
      <div class="gloss-entry"><span class="gloss-term"><span class="gloss-sym">M</span> Monad</span><div class="gloss-def">The dimensionless metaphysical origin-point of all grounded spirits. Not derivable from archetypal differentiation (Axiom II, Book I). Sustains all spirits without being numerically identical to any of them.<span class="gloss-cross">See: Grounded Spirit, Origin Irreducibility, Ground-Responsibility</span></div></div>
      <div class="gloss-entry"><span class="gloss-term"><span class="gloss-sym">C₁₂</span> Archetypal Field</span><div class="gloss-def">The rotationally symmetric twelvefold manifold of structured identity through which all embodied spirits are individuated. Locally closed under internal operations (Axiom I). Overlaid in Document 3 with the twelve zodiacal sectors.<span class="gloss-cross">See: Local Closure, Zodiacal Overlay, Archetypal Integrity</span></div></div>
      <div class="gloss-entry"><span class="gloss-term"><span class="gloss-sym">T</span> Toroidal Recursion</span><div class="gloss-def">The repetition of archetypal differentiation across temporal or experiential cycles within C₁₂. Persists indefinitely absent effective axial participation (Axiom III). Treated ethically as curriculum (Prop. E3, Book II).<span class="gloss-cross">See: Spiral Mediation, Recursion Discernment</span></div></div>
      <div class="gloss-entry"><span class="gloss-term"><span class="gloss-sym">S</span> Spiral Mediation</span><div class="gloss-def">A continuous trajectory intersecting all archetypal sectors of C₁₂ while asymptotically increasing participation in A. Composed of local internal operations at each finite stage but achieving a trans-structural effect at its limit.<span class="gloss-cross">See: Axial Operator, Universal Traversal, Gentle Ascent</span></div></div>
      <div class="gloss-entry"><span class="gloss-term"><span class="gloss-sym">A</span> Axial Operator</span><div class="gloss-def">A transformation-type orthogonal to the symmetry of C₁₂, capable of recontextualizing C₁₂ into a higher-dimensional open manifold (Def. 5, Book I). Not an internal symmetry operation (Axiom IV). Corresponds to the "13th principle" — the Ophiuchan axis beyond the closed twelve-fold field.<span class="gloss-cross">See: Liberation, Dimensional Upgrade, Axial Orientation</span></div></div>
      <div class="gloss-entry"><span class="gloss-term"><span class="gloss-sym">E</span> Embodiment</span><div class="gloss-def">Localization of a spirit's experience within C₁₂ under recursive conditions T. The sixth operator in the generative sequence M → C₁₂ → T → S → A → E.<span class="gloss-cross">See: Grounded Spirit, Toroidal Recursion</span></div></div>
      <div class="gloss-entry"><span class="gloss-term">Grounded Spirit</span><div class="gloss-def">A center of experience metaphysically grounded in M and phenomenologically individuated within C₁₂ (Def. 9, Book I). Distinct from formulations asserting numerical identity with M; employs the relation <span class="gloss-sym">GroundedIn(s, M)</span> to preserve individuation while maintaining shared monadic ground.<span class="gloss-cross">See: Monad, Ground-Phenomenology Duality</span></div></div>
      <div class="gloss-entry"><span class="gloss-term">Local Closure</span><div class="gloss-def">The property of C₁₂ whereby all operations strictly internal to it preserve its archetypal structure (Axiom I, revised). "Local" scopes Axiom I to operations with axial coordinate zero — resolving the Self-Escape Paradox.<span class="gloss-cross">See: Trans-structural Operation, Axiom VI</span></div></div>
      <div class="gloss-entry"><span class="gloss-term">Liberation</span><div class="gloss-def">A global transformation in which a spirit's experiential manifold changes from locally closed confinement to a vertically extensible open structure via effective participation in A (Def. 8, Book I). Occurs iff: M remains primary, S has traversed all sectors, and trans-structural axial reorientation is achieved (Theorem I).<span class="gloss-cross">See: Conditional Transcendence, Corollary 2 (Book I)</span></div></div>
      <div class="gloss-entry"><span class="gloss-term">Symbolic Axiality</span><div class="gloss-def">Conceptual or imagined alignment with A that has not been grounded in completed spiral traversal. Formally <span class="gloss-sym">A_symbolic</span> vs. <span class="gloss-sym">A_effective</span>. Produces dissociation rather than liberation.<span class="gloss-cross">See: Premature Alignment Paradox, False Liberation</span></div></div>
      <div class="gloss-entry"><span class="gloss-term">Spiral Wholeness</span><div class="gloss-def">The meta-ideal of the complete system (Theorem E1, Book II): a way of being continually returning to C₁₂'s multiplicity while integrating it in service of axial participation. Expressed in the Book II Scholium: "centered in M, wide in C₁₂, patient in T, inclined toward A, spiral in S."<span class="gloss-cross">See: Liberated Integrator, Gentle Ascent</span></div></div>
      <div class="gloss-entry"><span class="gloss-term">Zodiacal Overlay</span><div class="gloss-def">The interpretive layer applied to C₁₂ in Document 3, mapping each of the twelve archetypal sectors onto a zodiacal sign, sector theme, virtue, and two characteristic vices. Treated as a phenomenological instrument rather than an independent metaphysical claim


</body>
